/*
:name: tup_out_cond_whole
:type: equiv
:verilog_top: top
:pyrope_top: top
*/

// FAILING regression for 2i-issues D (residual): a tuple-typed OUTPUT port driven
// by a CONDITIONAL whole-tuple write. The flat unconditional whole-tuple write
// (tup_out_port) now lowers, but try_rewrite_port_whole_store does NOT handle a
// whole-store whose RHS is an if-expression: today this compiles with exit 0 and
// NO diagnostic yet SILENTLY MISCOMPILES — cgen emits only the else arm
// (\p.first=3, \p.second=4) and drops the `if c` entirely (lgcheck REFUTES;
// iverilog: c=1 -> (3,4), should be (1,2)). RED until the conditional whole-tuple
// write drives the flattened leaves per arm.
pub comb top(c:bool) -> (p:(first:u8, second:u8)) {
  p = if c { (first=1, second=2) } else { (first=3, second=4) }
}
